data.enText: to give a description of the main facts or points involved in sth

data.chText: 我们向委员会提纲挈领地讲了讲我们的提案。
data.enText: We outlined our proposals to the committee.

data.chText: 显示…的轮廓；勾勒…的外形
data.enText: to show or mark the outer edge of sth

data.chText: 他们看见了在天空的映衬下那座巨大建筑的轮廓。
data.enText: They saw the huge building outlined against the sky.
a description of the main facts or points involved in sth

data.chText: 这就是事件的简要情况。
data.enText: This is a brief outline of the events.

data.chText: 你应该为文章草拟个计划或提纲。
data.enText: You should draw up a plan or outline for the essay.

data.chText: 本书扼要叙述了主要的研究结果。
data.enText: The book describes in outline the main findings of the research.
the line that goes around the edge of sth, showing its main shape but not the details

data.chText: 我们终于能看到一小岛朦胧的轮廓了。
data.enText: At last we could see the dim outline of an island.

data.chText: 她简略地勾勒出人物的轮廓。
data.enText: She drew the figures in outline .

simple_means.memory_skill: out 外面 + line 直线，线条 → 外面的线 → 轮廓

tr: a sketchy summary of the main points of an argument or theory
the line that appears to bound an object
describe roughly or briefly or give the main points or summary of
example: sketch the outline of the book

tr: draw up an outline or sketch for something

value.def: If you outline an idea or a plan, you explain it in a general way.

example.ex: The mayor outlined his plan to clean up the town's image...
example.tran: 市长概述了他整顿市容的计划。

example.ex: The methods outlined in this book are only suggestions.
example.tran: 本书概括的一些方法仅供参考。

value.def: An outline is a general explanation or description of something.

example.ex: Following is an outline of the survey findings...
The proposals were given in outline by the Secretary of State.
example.tran: 国务卿对提议进行了简要的概述。

value.def: You say that an object is outlined when you can see its general shape because there is light behind it.

example.ex: The Ritz was outlined against the lights up there...
example.tran: 高悬的灯光映照出里兹饭店的轮廓。

example.ex: It was a beautiful sight outlined above the starry sky.

value.tran: （因背后的光线）显示…的轮廓（或外形）

value.def: The outline of something is its general shape, especially when it cannot be clearly seen.

example.ex: He could see only the hazy outline of the goalposts.
example.tran: 他只能看见球门柱模糊的轮廓。

partsOfSpeech.dec: air 空中 + line 直线，线条 → 航线
base 底部 + line 直线，线条 → 底线
border 边界 + line 直线，线条 → 边界，边缘
by 副的 + line 直线，线条 → 第二行 → 大标题下面写着作家姓名的一行 →〔报刊文章的〕署名行
date 日期 + line 直线，线条 → 国际日期变更线
partsOfSpeech.d: 国际日期变更线；日界线

partsOfSpeech.dec: dead 死 + line 直线，线条 → 死期，最后期限
de 使… + line 直线，线条 + ate 使… → 使构成线条 → 勾画；描写
guide 指导 + line 直线，线条 → 指导方针
hard 硬的 + line 直线，线条 → 强硬路线的；立场坚定的
partsOfSpeech.d: 强硬路线的；立场坚定的

partsOfSpeech.dec: head 头部 + line 直线，线条 → 写在文章第一行的内容 → 大字标题
partsOfSpeech.d: 大字标题；〔常作～s〕新闻提要

partsOfSpeech.dec: inter 在…之间 + line 直线，线条 → 写在行间
line 直线，线条 + age 总称 → 家谱 → 血统
line 直线，线条 + a …的 + ment 表名词 →〔人的〕线条 → 相貌特征
line 直线，线条 + ar …的 → 线的，直线的
line 直线，线条 + r → 定期飞机或定期船（沿着线飞）
partsOfSpeech.d: 定期飞机或定期船（沿着线飞）

partsOfSpeech.dec: out 外面 + line 直线，线条 → 外面的线 → 轮廓
touch 接近 + line 直线，线条 → 边线，界线
under 下 + line 直线，线条 → 在…下面画线；强调
